99
00:06:12.436 --> 00:06:16.396
rearranged leukemia, that KMT2A fusion protein actually binds

100
00:06:16.416 --> 00:06:20.056
with high affinity to menin at transcription start sites, and essentially

101
00:06:20.936 --> 00:06:24.676
pulls together a large active transcription complex that

102
00:06:24.696 --> 00:06:28.476
drives a leukemic transcription program, which is dominated by what's called a

103
00:06:28.496 --> 00:06:30.756
HOX/MEIS signature. So most

104
00:06:32.136 --> 00:06:35.116
leukemias are cells that are sensitive and menin have this HOX/MEIS signature.

105
00:06:35.636 --> 00:06:38.936
And that signature drives a leukemic transcription program that blocks

106
00:06:38.976 --> 00:06:42.926
differentiation, and essentially leads to self-renewal and proliferation and

107
00:06:42.976 --> 00:06:44.316
eventually acute leukemia.

108
00:06:45.136 --> 00:06:47.126
The menin inhibitors work, as shown on the right,

109
00:06:48.276 --> 00:06:51.716
rebumenib in this case, binds to menin with high affinity, blocks its

110
00:06:51.776 --> 00:06:55.665
interaction with the KMT2A fusion protein, and in so doing,

111
00:06:55.676 --> 00:06:59.466
breaks apart that transcription complex and essentially releases menin

112
00:06:59.596 --> 00:07:02.796
from chromatin. And once that transcription complex is gone,

113
00:07:03.296 --> 00:07:07.196
the leukemic transcription program collapses, and then the cells die

114
00:07:07.236 --> 00:07:09.556
from either differentiation or apoptosis.

